<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The Test:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
I used Bolt of Flame, 105 mana, evocation, because I wanted as many casts as possible, it was a fast spell (3.3 sec).  I started by leaving my ear open, the other ear had a Solist's Ear.  I wore the bracer, ring, and shawl.  I used no buffs at all.  I nuked till I could no longer cast more.  I tested this twice.<br>
<br>
Then I put on the earring, and took off the shawl, to balance out the mana.  Nuked till OOM twice, and then after the changes this morning, I did it one more time.  Also, 3 fizzles would equal enough mana for 1 cast.<br>
<br>
No Earring Test 1  -  41 casts, 1 fizzle<br>
No Earring Test 2  -  41 casts, 0 fizzles<br>
<br>
Earring Test 1  -  44 casts, 3 fizzles  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Earring Test 2  -  45 casts, 0 fizzles<br>
Earring Test 3  -  45 casts, 0 fizzles<br>
<br>
It appears to me that the earring saves ~10% mana on nukes and DoT's. <p>~~
